If the tool has a multi-turn flow (OTP-gated activation, double-entry PIN, etc.), expand the **lifecycle opts** column for each action using these tokens:

| token | meaning |
|-------|---------|
| `startsFlow=X` | this action opens flow `X` (or merges scratch data into it) |
| `requiresFlow=X` | refuse unless `currentFlow.name === X` |
| `endsFlow` | clears `currentFlow` + `awaitingInput` on `ok` |
| `issuesOtp→consumer` | this action mints an SCA challenge; library sets `awaitingInput=otp` for `consumer` |
| `requiresOtp` | refuse unless `awaitingInput.kind="otp"` for this action; auto-clears on `ok` |
| `startsMatchFor→consumer` | double-entry capturer; library sets `awaitingInput=match` for `consumer` |
| `requiresMatch(capturer, N)` | double-entry consumer; library decrements on `verdict: "match_mismatch"`, aborts on exhaustion |
| `soleStep` / `soleOnExecute` | batch-shape constraint (strict / relaxed-for-propose) |

